            Moreover, technology has democratized access to information and education. Online platforms like Coursera and Khan Academy offer courses from top universities to anyone with an internet connection. This has empowered millions of people to acquire new skills and improve their livelihoods. In this sense, technology is not merely a convenience but a catalyst for social mobility.

